chunk_content: That is, if an individual could be reported under both HTS_INDEX and another HTS_TST modality, that individual should only be reported once under HTS_INDEX. Again, the index modality under HTS_TST will auto-populate from HTS_INDEX (see HTS_INDEX reference sheet for more information). B. Provider Initiated Counseling and Testing (PITC): a. Emergency: Includes persons tested or seen in a designated emergency department or ward for the immediate care and treatment of an unforeseen illness or injury. 112 b. Inpatient: Includes PITC occurring among those patients admitted in the inpatient and surgery wards. c. Malnutrition: Clinics and inpatient wards predominately dedicated to the treatment of T E malnourished children.
